A function in SQL is something that takes a value → does something → returns a result
Think of it like a machin:
input → function → output
المدخلات ← الدالة ← المخرجات

🔸 Types of SQL Functions
    Aggregate Functions (work on MANY rows)
    Function          	What it does
SUM()	        |           total
COUNT()       |        	number of rows
AVG()	        |         average
MAX()         |        	biggest value
MIN()	        |         smallest value


exmp:
SELECT SUM(price) FROM orders;///IMPORTANT
Single Row Functions (work on ONE row)
UPPER(name) → makes text uppercase
LOWER(name) → lowercase
LENGTH(name) → number of characters
exmpl:
SELECT UPPER(name) FROM users;



Now we mix functions with GROUP BY 
SELECT customer, COUNT(*) AS total_orders
FROM orders
GROUP BY customer;
Show customers who spent more than 100

SELECT customer, SUM(price) AS total
FROM orders
GROUP BY customer
HAVING SUM(price) > 100;
